Chapter Conclusion
This chapter demonstrates that algorithmic images are increasingly participating in processes historically associated with sacred artifacts. Through generative consistency, ritualized interaction, and institutional validation, digital images acquire aura-like qualities and symbolic authority.
Digital sacredness thus emerges as a structural effect of computational environments rather than as a continuation of traditional religious systems. The ritualization of algorithmic images signals the formation of new cultural ontologies in which perception, technology, and belief converge.
